<!-- PROBLEM -->
<section class="problem">
  <div class="problem-inner">
    <div class="section-tag">The reality</div>
    <h2>Ops shouldn't be the thing that slows you down</h2>
    <p class="problem-lead">You know the drill. The supply chain stuff that was manageable at launch gets heavier as you grow. Here's where we see brands losing the most time and money.</p>
    <div class="pain-grid">
      <div class="pain-card">
        <h3>Everything lives in spreadsheets</h3>
        <p>Ingredients, suppliers, POs, delivery dates. It works until it doesn't, and by then you've already missed a restock window.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pain-card">
        <h3>Deliveries you can't rely on</h3>
        <p>When your on-time rate hovers around 60%, every week is a gamble. Late ingredients mean late production, and retailers don't wait around.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pain-card">
        <h3>Cash tied up in ingredients</h3>
        <p>You're paying suppliers before your customers have paid you. That gap gets wider as you scale, and it limits what you can say yes to.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pain-card">
        <h3>Your week disappears into admin</h3>
        <p>Chasing supplier confirmations, reconciling invoices, placing reorders. The work that keeps the lights on is the same work keeping you from growing.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

